12/11/2002
BELGRADE, Yugoslavia -- A national conference on the integration of refugees and internally displaced people started Monday (11 November) in Belgrade. 
The conference will focus on implementation of the national strategy for resolving the problems of refugees, approved by the Serbian government earlier this year. 
Speaking at the forum, the chairman of the South East Europe Stability Pact Steering Group for Refugees, Soren Jessen Petersen, proposed the establishment of housing fund for displaced persons in the region. 
Projects run by the international community have already secured houses for some 8,000 people; another 1,200 houses are under construction. 
(Tanjug, B92 Radio and TV, Beta - 11/11/02)
